doc.author: Sandeep Bandi <sandeepb@avinetworks.com>
description: Given an object_type, fetch all the objects of that type or fetch the specific object that matches the name/uuid given via options.
For single object lookup. If you want the output to be a list, you may want to pass option wantlist=True to the plugin.
notes: For more information on using Ansible to manage Avi Network devices see U(https://www.ansible.com/ansible-avi-networks).

options.name: api_context
description: Avi API context that includes current session ID and CSRF Token.
This allows user to perform single login and re-use the session.

options.name: api_version
description: Avi API version of to use for Avi API and objects.

options.name: avi_credentials
description: Avi Credentials dictionary which can be used in lieu of enumerating Avi Controller login details.

suboptions.name: api_version
description: Avi controller version

suboptions.name: controller
description: Avi controller IP or SQDN

suboptions.name: csrftoken
description: Avi controller API csrftoken to reuse existing session with session id

suboptions.name: password
description: Avi controller password

suboptions.name: port
description: Avi controller port

suboptions.name: session_id
description: Avi controller API session id to reuse existing session with csrftoken

suboptions.name: tenant
description: Avi controller tenant

suboptions.name: tenant_uuid
description: Avi controller tenant UUID

suboptions.name: timeout
description: Avi controller request timeout

suboptions.name: token
description: Avi controller API token

suboptions.name: username
description: Avi controller username

options.name: avi_disable_session_cache_as_fact
description: It disables avi session information to be cached as a fact.

options.name: controller
description: IP address or hostname of the controller. The default value is the environment variable C(AVI_CONTROLLER).

options.name: obj_name
description: name of the object to query

options.name: obj_type
description: type of object to query

options.name: obj_uuid
description: UUID of the object to query

options.name: password
description: Password of Avi user in Avi controller. The default value is the environment variable C(AVI_PASSWORD).

options.name: tenant
description: Name of tenant used for all Avi API calls and context of object.

options.name: tenant_uuid
description: UUID of tenant used for all Avi API calls and context of object.

options.name: username
description: Username used for accessing Avi controller. The default value is the environment variable C(AVI_USERNAME).

doc.short_description: Look up ``Avi`` objects.

doc_strings.examples:
# Lookup query for all the objects of a specific type.
- debug: msg="{{ lookup('avi', avi_credentials=avi_credentials, obj_type='virtualservice') }}"
# Lookup query for an object with the given name and type.
- debug: msg="{{ lookup('avi', avi_credentials=avi_credentials, obj_name='vs1', obj_type='virtualservice', wantlist=True) }}"
# Lookup query for an object with the given UUID and type.
- debug: msg="{{ lookup('avi', obj_uuid='virtualservice-5c0e183a-690a-45d8-8d6f-88c30a52550d', obj_type='virtualservice') }}"
# We can replace lookup with query function to always the get the output as list.
# This is helpful for looping.
- debug: msg="{{ query('avi', obj_uuid='virtualservice-5c0e183a-690a-45d8-8d6f-88c30a52550d', obj_type='virtualservice') }}"

return.name: _raw
description: One ore more objects returned from ``Avi`` API.
